Meatpacking DistrictHome › Locations › Meatpacking District 















Meatpacking District
Sugar Factory American Brasserie has settled into its new home at 835 Washington Street in New York City’s Meatpacking District, continuing the celebrated brand’s impressive worldwide expansion.
The new 9,000-square-foot brasserie and retail store delivers the same candyland appeal that has made Sugar Factory an international favorite. The design combines form and function to bring Sugar Factory’s whimsical brand into its new home on Washington Street. The dining room spans two floors, with 250 seats and two magnificent bars serving up Sugar Factory’s famed cocktail concoctions. The top floor also features a private “VIP” room that can be rented out for special events and comes complete with a personal candy store that can be customized with guests’ favorites.
The third and underground levels feature the Sugar Factory Chocolate Lounge with 68 seats, offering a wide array of cocktails with chocolate pairings. Glassware will be presented with a decadent chocolate rim as guests can enjoy a selection of fondues, cheeses, crepes Suzette and more.
Situated at the entrance to the new Sugar Factory American Brasserie, a spacious sidewalk café welcomes patrons with a 60 seat outdoor patio and to-go window serving artisanal doughnuts and 12 different flavors of gelato year-round.
The retail section features a selection of more than 300 of the company’s signature treats and merchandise, including candy bins and the world-famous Couture Pops. Synonymous with the Sugar Factory brand, Couture Pops have become a pop culture phenomenon and have made confections a celebrity accessory.
The expansive restaurant serves delectable breakfast, lunch, dinner and late-night options, offering a variety of inventive and mouthwatering appetizers, oversized sandwiches, salads, pizzas and more. Sugar Factory’s specialty, of course, is a sprawling dessert menu, featuring an assortment of warm, freshly-baked waffles and crepes, childhood favorites and rich, gourmet chocolates cascading from colossal fondue fountains. In addition to the savory cuisine and sweet confections, Sugar Factory offers a distinctive selection of liquid libations.
Book now








